<br>
As long as the secondary weapon is faster than the primary, or at least equal, it will always be available for a dual wield attack should the roll for it be successful. If the secondary delay is higher(slower) than the primary, you will miss every second chance at a dual wield attack after a successful secondary attack is attempted.<br>
<br>
I hope this makes sense, It does sound confusing.<br>
<br>
To make it simple, for best results use your BEST dmg/dly ratio weapon in Primary, then use in your secondary the highest damage weapon you have that is equal to or faster than your primary weapon.<br>
<br>
Aren <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uzellasaryrn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZellaSaryrn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(6/1/01 7:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duel Weilding</span><hr size=1> I beg to differ.<br>
