<br>
Only the primary hand gets damage bonuses based on level.<br>
<br>
Primary hand hits more often since you require your duel skill to go off to swing the offhand weapon.<br>
<br>
If your on and offhand weapons have the same delay, put the higher damage one in the primary hand.  Otherwise, put the faster one in the primary because you get your dam bonuses (assuming the weapons are similar dam/del).<br>
<br>
Many people will argue that since the offhand swings less you want a high dam slow weapon in offhand.  Frankly I dont think it matters one way or the other.   FAST FAST FAST weapon in primary, and high dam/del ratio in offhand.<br>
<br>
